properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 4 at 10:03PM CST until February 6 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant HIll MO
properties.description:
...Winter Weather Tuesday and Wednesday...

Snow chances will increase across the region by Wednesday
morning. Expect the most accumulating snow across central
Missouri into the Ozarks and southeastern Kansas. however, light
snow is possible as far north as the highway 36 corridor in
northern Missouri eastward into north-central and northeast
Missouri.

* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of 1 to 3 inches.

* WHERE...Portions of north central and northeast Missouri.

* WHEN...Until midnight CST Wednesday night.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1 in Kansas or visiting
traveler.modot.org in Missouri.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT CST WEDNESDAY NIGHT
